sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Browser
    participant Django as Django (views.py)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant S3 as S3 / RustFS
    participant Celery as Celery Worker
    participant Doit as doit + papermill
    participant Notebooks as Notebooks (steps/)

    User->>Browser: Upload CSV/Parquet file
    Browser->>Django: POST /flows/upload/
    Django->>S3: Upload raw file → raw/flows/{run_id}/input.*
    Django->>DB: Create FlowExecution (status=PENDING)
    Django->>Celery: run_pipeline_task.delay(run_id, s3_path, ...)
    Django-->>Browser: 200 + HTMX poll trigger

    loop Poll every 2s until terminal status
        Browser->>Django: GET /flows/{run_id}/status/
        Django->>DB: Read FlowExecution.status
        Django-->>Browser: HTMX partial (status badge)
    end

    Celery->>DB: Update status → RUNNING
    Celery->>Doit: subprocess doit pipeline (PIPELINE_PARAMS env)

    Doit->>Notebooks: papermill 01_ingest.ipynb
    Notebooks->>S3: Read raw input
    Notebooks->>S3: Write processed/flows/{run_id}/01_raw.parquet
    Notebooks-->>Doit: JSON output (row_count)

    Doit->>Notebooks: papermill 02_validate.ipynb
    Notebooks->>S3: Read 01_raw.parquet
    Notebooks->>S3: Write 02_validated.parquet

    Doit->>Notebooks: papermill 03_transform.ipynb
    Notebooks->>S3: Read 02_validated.parquet
    Notebooks->>S3: Write 03_transformed.parquet

    Doit->>Notebooks: papermill 04_aggregate.ipynb
    Notebooks->>S3: Read 03_transformed.parquet
    Notebooks->>S3: Write output.parquet

    Doit-->>Celery: Exit 0 + stdout with JSON metadata
    Celery->>DB: Update FlowExecution (status=COMPLETED, row_count, s3_output_path)

    Browser->>Django: GET /flows/{run_id}/status/
    Django-->>Browser: HTMX partial (COMPLETED + link to results)
    User->>Browser: Click "View Results"
    Browser->>Django: GET /flows/{run_id}/results/
    Django->>S3: DuckDB query output.parquet (preview 100 rows)
    Django-->>Browser: Results table + summary stats
